parameters.name: obj_p
parameters.description:
A pointer to the object you want to release.
  This can be a pointer to an ACL, an ACL qualifier, or a string allocated by one of the ACL functions.

full_content:
Function: acl_free
URL: https://www.qnx.com/developers/docs/7.1/com.qnx.doc.neutrino.lib_ref/topic/a/acl_free.html
Synopsis: int acl_free( void *obj_p );
Headers: #include <sys/acl.h>
Parameters:
  - obj_p: A pointer to the object you want to release.
  This can be a pointer to an ACL, an ACL qualifier, or a string allocated by one of the ACL functions.
Examples:
Example 1:
#include <sys/acl.h>

int acl_free( void *obj_p );
